main

Class Behavior

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.Behavior

  • public class Behavior
extends java.lang.Object
    This class handles the movements and behaviors of each different Ant Type. It also controls the generation of food and the effects of an Ant touching food tiles.

      • moveRandom

        public void moveRandom(Ant ant,
                       Tile[][] screen)
        Makes an Ant randomly shift position to an adjacent position in the world. There are eight possible movements: up, down, left, right, up-left, up-right, down-left, and down-right.
        Parameters:
        ant - The ant that will be moved.
        screen - The array the ant moves through.

      • moveRandomCross

        Parameters:

        screen - The array the ant moves through.

      • moveRandomDiag

        public void moveRandomDiag(Ant ant,

        screen - The array the ant moves through.

      • digToBottom

        public void digToBottom(Queen ant,
                        Tile[][] screen)
        Makes the ant move vertically down in random horizontal directions until it reaches row 70. At Row 70, the ant stops going down, its current position is set as the location of the nest, and finally buildHive() is called to create the nest.
        Parameters:
        ant - The ant that will be moved.
        screen - The array the ant moves through.

      • buildHive

        private void buildHive(Queen ant,
                       Tile[][] screen)
        Makes an ant move a randomly move around its nest area, creating a small, dug out pit. From then on, new Ants will spawn in the nest area.
        Parameters:
        ant - The ant that will be moved.
        screen - The array the ant moves through.

      • moveBackNW

        private boolean moveBackNW(Ant ant,
                           Tile[][] screen)
        Moves an Ant away from the world boundary in a north-west direction. This only happens if the ant is currently out of bounds.
        Parameters:
        ant - The ant that will be moved.
        screen - The array the ant moves through.
        Returns:
        True if the Ant was out of bounds, False if not.
